<h3 class="page-header">Register for RailsBridge!</h3>

<p>RailsBridge Montreal wants to democratize software development for everyone eager to learn by providing a free one-day-and-a-half event that teaches how to build software applications using the Ruby programming language and Ruby on Rails web development technology. Ruby and Ruby on Rails are the easiest technologies to learn to develop software, whether professionally or just for fun. After a successful first event this spring, we are back for another round.</p>
<p>
  We are offering three different levels in French and English:
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Beginner</strong>: An introduction to programming done in Ruby. This level is for people who have never tried software development before.</li>
    <li><strong>Intermediate</strong>: An introduction to Rails. This level is for people who have some programming knowledge but have never used Ruby on Rails before.</li>
    <li><strong>Advanced</strong>: For people with a some knowledge of web development and Rails specifically who would like to expand their horizons.</li>
  </ul>
</p>
<p>During the workshop, the number of students assigned to each teacher/TA (teaching assistant) is kept as low as possible so that students have an easy access to experienced developers that can answer questions. Everything takes place in a casual atmosphere where people learn at their own pace and have fun while doing so.</p>
<p>The curriculums are adjusted at every event to follow the learning progression of the participants. By attending RailsBridge Montreal, you will learn how to build software applications, meet a lot of interesting people, and have fun. We look forward to your registration.</p>
<p>If you have questions about the curriculum or need help choosing your level, please do not hesitate to contact us at railsbridgemontreal@gmail.com.</p>
<p>Please note, it is not possible to take more than one level, since they take place at the same time.</p>

